{"word":"H7848 - שִׁטָּה - shiṭṭâh - shit-taw' - Shittah","slug":"H7848","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שִׁטָּה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shiṭṭâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shit-taw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Shittah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D8;&#x05BC;&#x05D9;&#x05DD;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05D8;&#x05BC;&#x05D4; - shit&#x0323;t&#x0323;a&#x0302;h  shit&#x0323;t&#x0323;&#x0131;&#x0302;ym</b> - <i>shit-taw', shit-teem'</i><p/>Feminine of a derivative (the second form being only in the plural, meaning the <i>sticks of wood</i>) from the same as <a href=\"#/H7850\">H7850</a>; the <i>acacia</i> (from its <i>scourging</i> thorns): - shittah, shittim. See also <a href=\"#/H1029\">H1029</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4889\">H4889</a>, <a href=\"#/H4892\">H4892</a>, <a href=\"#/H4893\">H4893</a>, <a href=\"#/H516\">H516</a>, <a href=\"#/H7843\">H7843</a>, <a href=\"#/H7851\">H7851</a>"}]}